@startuml OnlineShoppingSystem_ClassDiagram

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor #333333
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Online Shopping System</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Customer searches product, adds to cart, places order, pays, tracks delivery." Step 1 to 8.</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
package "Entry Point" as EP #E8EAF6 {
    class OnlineShoppingSystem <<Facade>> {
        - customers : Map
        - orders : Map
        - products : Map
        - paymentService : PaymentService
        - orderService : OrderService
        - searchService : SearchService
        --
        + {static} getInstance() : OnlineShoppingSystem
        + registerCustomer(name, email, addr) : Customer
        + placeOrder(customerId, items, strategy) : Order
        + searchProducts(query) : List
        + getShoppingCart(customerId) : ShoppingCart
    }
}

note top of EP #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.** "Customer visits our
    platform. Client only talks to this **Facade**.
    Hides all internal services behind one API."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: USER + PRODUCT MODELS
' ====================================================================
package "User Management" as UM #E8F5E9 {
    class Customer {
        - id : String
        - name : String
        - email : String
        - account : Account
        - shippingAddress : Address
        - orders : List
        --
        + getOrderHistory() : List
    }

    class Account {
        - username : String
        - password : String
        - cart : ShoppingCart
        --
        + authenticate(password) : boolean
    }

    class Address {
        - street : String
        - city : String
        - state : String
        - zipCode : String
        - country : String
    }

    Customer *-right- Account : has >
    Customer *-down- Address : lives at >
}

note top of UM #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2a** - "Customer has Account (auth)
    and Address (shipping). Account
    holds the ShoppingCart." **(SRP)**
end note

package "Product Catalog" as PC #E8F5E9 {
    interface Product <<Interface>> {
        + getName() : String
        + getPrice() : double
        + getCategory() : ProductCategory
        + getDescription() : String
    }

    class BaseProduct <<ConcreteProduct>> {
        - id : String
        - name : String
        - price : double
        - description : String
        - category : ProductCategory
    }

    enum ProductCategory {
        CLOTHING
        ELECTRONICS
        GROCERY
        BOOKS
    }

    Product <|.. BaseProduct
    BaseProduct -right-> ProductCategory
}

note top of PC #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2b** - "Products use an interface.
    BaseProduct is the default. Why interface?
    Because Decorator pattern needs it..."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: SEARCH + DECORATOR
' ====================================================================
package "Search" as SS #EFEBE9 {
    class SearchService <<Service>> {
        - productCatalog : Collection
        --
        + searchByName(query) : List
        + searchByCategory(cat) : List
        + filterByPriceRange(min, max) : List
    }
}

package "Product Decoration" as PD #FFF3E0 {
    abstract class ProductDecorator <<Decorator>> {
        # wrappedProduct : Product
        --
        + getName() : String
        + getPrice() : double
    }

    class GiftWrapDecorator <<ConcreteDecorator>> {
        - wrapCost : double
        - wrapDescription : String
        --
        + getPrice() : double
        + getDescription() : String
    }

    Product <|.. ProductDecorator
    ProductDecorator o-up-> Product : wraps >
    ProductDecorator <|-- GiftWrapDecorator
}

note bottom of PD #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3** - "Customer searches, finds product,
    wants gift wrap. Instead of subclass explosion,
    **Decorator** adds cost at runtime:
    new GiftWrapDecorator(baseProduct)"
    **Pattern: Decorator | OCP**
end note

SearchService -down-> Product : searches >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: SHOPPING CART
' ====================================================================
package "Shopping Cart" as SC #F3E5F5 {
    class ShoppingCart {
        - items : Map
        --
        + addItem(product, qty) : void
        + removeItem(productId) : void
        + getItems() : Map
        + clearCart() : void
        + getTotal() : double
    }

    class CartItem {
        - quantity : int
        - product : Product
        --
        + getSubtotal() : double
    }

    ShoppingCart *-- CartItem : contains >
}

note bottom of SC #E1BEE7
    **STEP 4** - "Customer adds (decorated)
    product to cart. Cart holds CartItems.
    On 'Place Order', cart items become
    OrderLineItems."
end note

CartItem -down-> Product : references >
Account -down-> ShoppingCart : owns >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: ORDER + SERVICES
' ====================================================================
package "Order Management" as OM #FFEBEE {
    class Order <<Context>> {
        - id : String
        - customer : Customer
        - status : OrderStatus
        - currentState : OrderState
        - shippingAddress : Address
        - items : List
        - orderDate : LocalDateTime
        - observers : List
        --
        + shipOrder() : void
        + deliverOrder() : void
        + cancelOrder() : void
        + registerObserver(o) : void
        + notifyObservers() : void
    }

    class OrderLineItem {
        - quantity : int
        - price : double
        - product : Product
        --
        + getLineTotal() : double
    }

    enum OrderStatus {
        PLACED
        SHIPPED
        PENDING_PAYMENT
        DELIVERED
        CANCELLED
        RETURNED
    }

    Order *-- OrderLineItem : contains >
    Order -right-> OrderStatus : tracks >
}

note top of OM #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5** - "OrderService validates stock via
    InventoryService, creates Order. Order is the
    **central object** — it uses **State Pattern**
    (lifecycle) and **Observer Pattern** (notifications)."
end note

package "Order Services" as OS #EFEBE9 {
    class OrderService <<Service>> {
        - inventoryService : InventoryService
        --
        + createOrder(customer, items) : Order
        + validateOrder(order) : boolean
    }

    class InventoryService <<Service>> {
        - stock : Map
        --
        + checkStock(productId) : boolean
        + updateStock(productId, qty) : void
    }

    OrderService -right-> InventoryService : checks stock >
}

OrderLineItem -down-> Product : for >
Customer -down-> Order : places >
OrderService -down-> Order : creates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: STATE PATTERN
' ====================================================================
package "Order State Machine" as SM #FCE4EC {
    interface OrderState <<State>> {
        + handleOrder(order) : void
        + shipOrder(order) : void
        + deliverOrder(order) : void
        + cancelOrder(order) : void
    }

    class PlacedState <<ConcreteState>> {
        + shipOrder(order) : void
        + cancelOrder(order) : void
    }

    class ShippedState <<ConcreteState>> {
        + deliverOrder(order) : void
        + cancelOrder(order) : void
    }

    class DeliveredState <<ConcreteState>> {
        + handleOrder(order) : void
    }

    class CancelledState <<ConcreteState>> {
        + handleOrder(order) : void
    }

    OrderState <|.. PlacedState
    OrderState <|.. ShippedState
    OrderState <|.. DeliveredState
    OrderState <|.. CancelledState
}

note bottom of SM #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6** - "Without this, Order has huge if-else
    chains. **State Pattern**: each state is a class.
    PlacedState can ship/cancel. ShippedState can
    deliver/cancel. Terminal: Delivered, Cancelled."
    Placed -> Shipped -> Delivered
    Placed -> Cancelled | Shipped -> Cancelled
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

Order -down-> OrderState : delegates lifecycle >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: OBSERVER PATTERN
' ====================================================================
package "Notifications" as NM #E0F7FA {
    interface Subject <<Observable>> {
        + registerObserver(o) : void
        + removeObserver(o) : void
        + notifyObservers() : void
    }

    interface OrderObserver <<Observer>> {
        + update(order) : void
    }

    class EmailNotificationObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
        - emailAddress : String
        --
        + update(order) : void
    }

    class PushNotificationObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
        - deviceToken : String
        --
        + update(order) : void
    }

    OrderObserver <|.. EmailNotificationObserver
    OrderObserver <|.. PushNotificationObserver
    Subject -right-> OrderObserver : notifies >
}

note bottom of NM #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7** - "On every state change, Order
    calls notifyObservers(). **Observer Pattern**:
    Order doesn't know how to send email/push.
    Add SMS? One new observer. Order unchanged."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

Order .up.|> Subject


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: PAYMENT — Strategy
' ====================================================================
package "Payment" as PM #EDE7F6 {
    class PaymentService <<Service>> {
        --
        + processPayment(strategy, amount) : boolean
    }

    interface PaymentStrategy <<Strategy>> {
        + pay(amount) : boolean
    }

    class CreditCardPaymentStrategy <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
        - cardNumber : String
        - expiryDate : String
        --
        + pay(amount) : boolean
    }

    class UpiPaymentStrategy <<ConcreteStrategy>> {
        - upiId : String
        --
        + pay(amount) : boolean
    }

    PaymentService -right-> PaymentStrategy : delegates >
    PaymentStrategy <|.. CreditCardPaymentStrategy
    PaymentStrategy <|.. UpiPaymentStrategy
}

note bottom of PM #D1C4E9
    **STEP 8** - "Customer pays. How they pay varies:
    credit card, UPI, wallet. **Strategy Pattern**:
    PaymentService delegates to PaymentStrategy.
    Add PayPal? One new class. Nothing else changes."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "We traced: register -> search -> decorate (gift wrap)
    -> cart -> order -> pay -> state transitions -> notifications.
    5 patterns: **Facade**, **Decorator**, **State**, **Observer**, **Strategy**.
    Each solves a specific problem. All extensible via OCP."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  CROSS-MODULE
' ====================================================================
OnlineShoppingSystem -down-> Customer : manages >
OnlineShoppingSystem -down-> OrderService
OnlineShoppingSystem -down-> PaymentService
OnlineShoppingSystem -down-> SearchService


' ====================================================================
'  LAYOUT
' ====================================================================
EP -[hidden]down-> UM
EP -[hidden]down-> PC
PC -[hidden]down-> PD
PC -[hidden]down-> SS
UM -[hidden]down-> SC
SC -[hidden]down-> OM
OM -[hidden]down-> OS
OM -[hidden]down-> SM
SM -[hidden]down-> NM
NM -[hidden]down-> PM
PM -[hidden]down-> WRAPUP


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Customer visits, registers via Facade | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Customer/Account/Address + Product/BaseProduct models | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Customer searches, picks product, adds gift wrap | Decorator | OCP |
    | 4 | Adds to ShoppingCart, CartItem references Product | -- | SRP |
    | 5 | Places order, stock validated, Order created | -- | SRP |
    | 6 | Order transitions: Placed -> Shipped -> Delivered | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 7 | On each state change, email/push observers notified | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Payment via CreditCard / UPI strategy | Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Register + Search** = Steps 1-3 | **Cart + Order** = Steps 4-5 | **Lifecycle + Pay** = Steps 6-8 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
